Interactive Calculator Application

Overview

This project is an interactive calculator application developed for a course assignment. It demonstrates the use of Python functions, widgets, and error handling to perform basic arithmetic operations. The application is hosted in a Google Colab notebook, leveraging interactive widgets for seamless user experience.

Arithmetic Operations:
Addition
Subtraction
Multiplication
Division (with error handling for division by zero)
Exponentiation
Square Root (with error handling for negative inputs)

Interactive User Interface:
Dropdown menu to select operations.
Inputs for entering numbers.
A "Calculate" button to run the calculation.
Real-time display of the result.

Example:
Operation: Addition
First Number: 5
Second Number: 3
Result: 8
